Usually a project&#39;s pom in the Parent section has this information, which you can easily see if you happen to use Eclipse:

 - Group Id
 - Artifact Id
 - Version
 - Relative Path

Relative path indicates the path respect the position of your project folder in the form, for example, `../main-project/parent`

In your pom there should be another line in your `&lt;parent&gt;` declaration:

    &lt;parent&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;com.playtech.simulator&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;net&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;1.0-SNAPSHOT&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;relativePath&gt;path-to-your-parent-project&lt;/relativePath&gt;
    &lt;/parent&gt;

So revise your pom paying attention on where the projects are set.

